    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've prepared:\n\n## Plan: Add `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\nAfter thoroughly exploring the codebase, here's exactly what needs to happen across **4 files**:\n\n### 1. `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`\n- Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` enum (after `Size(SizeArgs)`)\n- Add `StatsArgs` struct right after `SizeArgs` — identical shape, just a `pub human: bool` field with the same `--human`/`-H`/`--human-readable` flags\n\n### 2. `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` *(new file)*\n- Mirrors `cache_size.rs` but loops over `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 buckets)\n- For each bucket: calls `cache.bucket(bucket)` → path, checks if path exists, uses `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` for size\n- Prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line (using `CacheBucket`'s `Display` impl → e.g. `\"wheels-v6\"`)\n- Prints `total: {total}` at the end\n- Handles `--human` flag with `human_readable_bytes` (already re-exported in `commands/mod.rs`)\n- **No** `preview` parameter (unlike `cache_size`)\n\n### 3. `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`\n- Add `mod cache_stats;` alongside `mod cache_size;`\n- Add `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the `cache_size` re-export\n\n### 4. `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- Add dispatch arm right after `CacheCommand::Size`: `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)`\n\nNo new crate dependencies needed — `diskus` is already in use.",
